Giuliano wanted to do a book about Lennon. The show presented Julia as an unfit mother, no mother at all, Baird said. Goldman knows the formula: the more sleaze, the more dough. She and her younger sister, Jacqui, grew up with their parents amid an extended family of aunts, uncles, cousins _ and big brother John. Giuliano was harsher. But mostly it tells of a mother and son who, while living apart, had a loving relationship. Baird has been accused of cashing in on her step-brother but insists she just wants to tell the family's story of Lennon's early years. 